Author: Clairety
Title: [ANN] [Pre-ICO] Clairety AI - 'End Fake News [LIVE]
Body: Apologies for the slow response.  Our main UI is a browser module which is distributed for free.  Users download and run the module and it parses the JSON from supported social media sites, inserting our score into the content.  Images are available in the whitepaper.  It doesn't run on user voting.  Rather we give each of the half billion social media contributors a rating based on our AI's assessment of their content, and then the user has the option to filter the content that they think scores 'too low' for them to be useful.  Some people want to see everything.  Some people only want to see the most credible information.  For some, it's a question of what they're looking to find out.  Sometimes they want pictures of angry cat which is fun, but not necessarily credible.  Sometime the question is an important one and they're only interested in 'the facts'.  With our system every user decides for themselves. And in the process, we use the power of the marketplace to deny 'clicks' to the most polarized sources and make the more credible news sources 'worth' more.

Author: Clairety
Title: [ANN] [Pre-ICO] Clairety AI - 'End Fake News [LIVE]
Body: Our core algorithms are US patent pending and represent proprietary business intelligence.  They will not be shared with the broader community.  We are however perfectly happy to talk about the results and 'why' it works.  Please stop by on our Telegram channels, available on our website, and ask away.

Author: Clairety
Title: [ANN] [Pre-ICO] Clairety AI - 'End Fake News [LIVE]
Body: We have a great deal of information written about this on our website, our whitepaper, and in Medium (links available at our website). We all tend to 'like' information that agrees with the views we already have.  In psychology this is called 'confirmation bias' or 'motivated reasoning'.  But what we 'like' may or may not be presented in a misleading way.  This is what we tell you.  If the 'news' you're reading is presented in a way that sheds light or a way that casts shadow.  'Trust' should be given to those who try to shed light, even if it isn't an opinion that we already hold.  We give our users the power to decide.

Author: Clairety
Title: [ANN] [Pre-ICO] Clairety AI - 'End Fake News [LIVE]
Body: We expect to release a beta sometime after Q3, 2018.  When precisely is difficult to say at this point.  But we're working as hard as we can to deliver it as soon as possible.
